2. Lenz J1772 (Female) to NACS (Male) Charging Adapter
The Lenz J1772 to Tesla charging adapter allows Tesla vehicle owners to charge their cars from public Level 2 charging stations that have a J1772 connection socket. This adapter fits securely into the charging port of Tesla Models 3, S, X, and Y. It is rated for 80 amps of current at 240 volts, suitable for Level 1 and Level 2 charging. The adapter houses premium copper alloy connector pins and has an IP54 rating, protecting it against dust and water.

Like the previously mentioned Lectron adapter, this unit presently serves Tesla owners exclusively. However, in the future, when Ford, GM, and other automakers begin incorporating NACS connectors into their electric vehicles, an adapter like this one will become necessary if you encounter non-NACS Level 1 and Level 2 chargers on your journey.

Pros:

Provides access to thousands of public charging stations across North America
Charging speeds of up to 80 amps allow charges to be completed faster.
Securely locks into place on both the Tesla vehicle and J1772 charger ports
Includes a carrying pouch for safe storage and organization in the car
2-year warranty and customer support from the manufacturer
Cons:

Adds an extra step compared to direct Tesla charging
Potential single point of failure versus built-in charging port
The hanging weight of the adapter could put stress on the vehicle charging inlet over time
